    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Small decorative cases for carrying visiting cards, which were small cards bearing the name, and sometimes the address of a person or married couple for presentation; prime examples date from 19th-century western nations.</Note_Text>
